				                <div>Hello Steve,<br />
The directory is absent because there is no specific directory to upload it to. Each person designs their site in different ways. Many may have a specific folder to upload the videos to, some will not. Maybe they put all videos in one folder, maybe they organize the content differently. It is a lot like a closet, each person has their own way of storing things. As long as it in the house (root directory of the site), then whichever room or closet it is stored in is up to you.<br />
<br />
Do know, however, that if you have it in a subfolder you will need to add that to the source path. For example, if the video is in your main root, it would appear as in the example:<br />
<div class="code_block">SRC="video.mp4"</div><br />
Whereas if it was in a subfolder named 'videos' then you need to specify that in the path:<br />
<div class="code_block">SRC="videos/video.mp4"</div><br />
<br />
Kindest Regards,<br />
Scott M</div>
